text: Best canteen food I've had in any camp they actually have vegetables! I had the fried rice with squid & lady's finger.

It is a popular Muslim stall inside Sungei Gedong Camp. The Nasi Padang was above average and priced below what you’d pay outside. The curry puff was large but airy, with an average taste. They also offer a value set for $3.80, which includes fried rice, a piece of chicken cutlet, and an egg.
Best. Always there for mee siam. Can’t add photo, have to eat there yourself.
